26:15.300 --> 26:18.000
Yes, yes. I-I was, um...

26:18.900 --> 26:20.000
I was aware of that.

26:20.800 --> 26:25.200
So if you're so
uncomfortable here, why come?

26:25.500 --> 26:26.500
Because...

26:27.600 --> 26:29.200
something goes on in here.

26:29.200 --> 26:30.200
He does something.

26:30.300 --> 26:32.000
And you want
to find out what it is.

26:32.100 --> 26:34.100
Dissect it so that you can
do it yourself.

26:34.200 --> 26:35.200
Yes.
So that

26:35.300 --> 26:36.800
you can do it without Booth.

26:36.900 --> 26:38.900
So that you won't
need him anymore.
No.

26:39.500 --> 26:40.500
No?
No,

26:40.600 --> 26:42.000
I just want to observe.

26:42.400 --> 26:44.100
Surely if you want to
observe, you can do that

26:44.200 --> 26:46.400
the other side of the
mirror there, instead of

26:46.800 --> 26:49.300
insisting on being
in this room with him,

26:49.400 --> 26:51.100
out of your element.

26:51.100 --> 26:54.500
Observation isn't just seeing,
Dr. Wyatt.

26:54.600 --> 26:56.000
It's experiencing.

26:56.400 --> 26:57.700
Ideally, I'd prefer being

26:58.000 --> 27:01.300
inside Booth's head...
you know, seeing

27:01.600 --> 27:03.500
and feeling things
the way he does.

27:03.900 --> 27:06.100
Then maybe I... I'd understand.

27:06.800 --> 27:08.400
Be one with him?

27:10.400 --> 27:12.100
In a scientific sense.

27:17.500 --> 27:18.500
Booth needs me.

27:18.600 --> 27:20.900
Hodgins has a line
on the murder weapon.

27:21.800 --> 27:22.900
Ta-ta, then.

27:23.200 --> 27:24.300
We're done here.

27:25.400 --> 27:26.300
Thanks.

27:29.800 --> 27:31.300
<i>We need to know what artifacts</i>

27:31.400 --> 27:33.600
were buried with Bishop Jursik.

27:33.900 --> 27:36.200
You see, there was no
photograph of his burial

27:36.300 --> 27:37.700
in the paperwork
that we received.

27:37.800 --> 27:39.200
Well, I'm not
allowed to pull

27:39.300 --> 27:40.500
internment records
without

27:40.600 --> 27:41.800
Father Donlan's
permission.

27:43.300 --> 27:44.100
Where is she going?

27:44.300 --> 27:45.200
Bones, Bones,
Bones, Bones.

27:45.400 --> 27:46.900
You are approaching the altar.

27:47.200 --> 27:49.500
Very sensitive area.

27:49.900 --> 27:50.300
Okay.

27:50.400 --> 27:51.600
All right, listen,
you must have known 

27:51.700 --> 27:53.700
Father McCourt pretty well.
Did him and Father Matt

27:54.000 --> 27:55.100
similar tastes?

27:55.100 --> 27:57.400
Look, the only
similarity I know of was

27:57.500 --> 27:58.700
that they were
from the same seminary.

27:58.800 --> 27:59.800
Same seminary?

28:00.400 --> 28:01.400
Look, Agent Booth,

28:01.600 --> 28:04.300
there's so much suspicion
and innuendo these days.

28:04.800 --> 28:05.800
This is a good parish.

28:06.100 --> 28:08.100
The Father makes sure of that.
What's that?

28:09.200 --> 28:10.600
It's the chalice.
Oh, no, it's,

28:10.700 --> 28:12.200
it's the vessel
in which the wine

28:12.300 --> 28:14.100
is transformed
into the blood of Christ.

28:14.100 --> 28:16.000
Don't touch it! No.
It is going to be touched,

28:16.100 --> 28:18.300
Booth, it's silver and
these little eagles

28:18.400 --> 28:20.200
are a common Napoleonic motif.

28:20.500 --> 28:21.400
You're saying
that it's, uh...

28:22.400 --> 28:23.600
possible that
this could be

28:24.300 --> 28:25.800
a murder weapon?
Yeah.

28:26.000 --> 28:28.300
Can we take this with us
or do we need to serve

28:28.400 --> 28:29.500
a warrant on God?

28:34.900 --> 28:36.300
It's a match.

28:36.700 --> 28:38.700
The silver fragments in
Father McCourt's skull

28:38.700 --> 28:40.100
came from that chalice.

28:40.200 --> 28:41.900
That officially
looks the least

28:42.000 --> 28:44.300
like a murder weapon than
any murder weapon I've seen.

28:44.400 --> 28:45.200
The green bone

28:45.300 --> 28:46.700
response indicated the injury

28:46.800 --> 28:48.300
was inflicted perimortem.

28:48.400 --> 28:49.300
That means he might've already

28:49.400 --> 28:50.900
been dead when he was struck.

28:50.900 --> 28:53.200
So we have no cause of death?
Yes, we do.

28:53.300 --> 28:54.600
McCourt was poisoned.

28:54.700 --> 28:56.100
An alkaloid called taxin.

28:56.200 --> 28:57.600
Could it have been accidental?

28:57.600 --> 28:59.100
Not at these concentrations.

28:59.200 --> 29:01.300
Well, I'll go compile a list
of possible sources

29:01.300 --> 29:02.500
of the poison at the church.

29:03.200 --> 29:04.900
So what if they went
to the same seminary?

29:05.000 --> 29:06.600
Well, then why didn't
Father Matt mention it, huh?

29:06.700 --> 29:08.700
What else is he not saying?
This is intuition, right?

29:08.800 --> 29:10.700
You're subconsciously
recalling pupil dilation

29:10.700 --> 29:12.100
or some pheromones?

29:12.200 --> 29:14.600
You know what?
We're not talking
the same language here.

29:15.600 --> 29:16.800
No, no, no.

29:16.900 --> 29:19.700
That's not a Butcher.
Come here, Tony.

29:19.800 --> 29:21.400
Why'd you always pick me,
Father? Take Sam.

29:22.200 --> 29:24.000
Let's go. Watch.

29:30.200 --> 29:32.300
Now from here,
Tony can reach around

29:32.400 --> 29:34.300
to my right arm.
He uses his left knee

29:34.400 --> 29:35.700
against my left hip and...

29:37.000 --> 29:38.900
Okay? Tony's in control.

29:39.200 --> 29:41.500
I'm helpless. And he can score
some back points.

29:42.300 --> 29:42.900
Good job, Tony.

29:43.000 --> 29:43.500
Let me up.

29:45.400 --> 29:46.400
That's the Butcher.

29:46.700 --> 29:48.300
Learn it, love it.

29:48.400 --> 29:49.900
Use it to smite your enemies

29:50.000 --> 29:51.700
in the name of our loving Lord.

29:52.200 --> 29:53.400
Pair up. Get it right.

29:55.700 --> 29:57.200
Kid took me down for real.

29:58.500 --> 30:00.200
That shot must not
be working, Doc.

30:00.700 --> 30:02.600
So... what can I
do for you today?

30:02.700 --> 30:04.800
Yeah, Father, I...
You and Father McCourt

30:05.000 --> 30:07.500
were in seminary
at the same time.
Right.

30:07.700 --> 30:09.100
But I told you, I never
met Father McCourt.

30:09.200 --> 30:10.400
What, you guys
never got together,

30:10.600 --> 30:12.200
compared wrestling moves?

30:13.400 --> 30:14.600
I didn't know him there.

30:14.900 --> 30:16.600
Did you know everyone
who went to your college?

30:16.800 --> 30:19.400
You do know why
Father McCourt was sent here.

30:19.600 --> 30:20.800
Yeah, I've heard the rumors.

30:20.900 --> 30:21.600
That's all.

30:22.500 --> 30:24.600
Do you base all your
investigations on rumors,

30:24.900 --> 30:25.900
Agent Booth?

30:26.100 --> 30:27.400
He has a point, Booth.

30:27.600 --> 30:28.900
You know,
St. Agatha's has been

30:29.000 --> 30:30.700
a dumping ground
for troubled priests

30:30.700 --> 30:33.300
for some time, so it's
reasonable to suggest

30:33.400 --> 30:35.300
that you're one of them.

30:37.000 --> 30:39.000
I told you why I was sent here.

30:41.900 --> 30:43.700
I got work to do.

30:55.200 --> 30:57.300
So you still think that
Father Donlan is the killer?

30:57.500 --> 30:58.800
I mean, Matt...

30:58.900 --> 31:00.800
could have killed McCourt
and taken his post.

31:00.800 --> 31:02.800
Why?
Because McCourt
was going to come

31:02.900 --> 31:03.800
clean about being a pedophile.

31:04.000 --> 31:06.800
Maybe accuse Matt, if
they knew each other.

31:07.300 --> 31:10.600
Of course... there's
no evidence of that.

31:11.100 --> 31:12.600
I have no intuition.

31:12.700 --> 31:14.700
None. Zilch.
And you have no

31:14.800 --> 31:16.500
analytical skills.
I mean, you're all about

31:16.900 --> 31:19.200
emotion and feeling.
Well...

31:19.300 --> 31:21.300
They say that means you
have a well developed
feminine side.

31:23.000 --> 31:24.200
Who? Who says that?

31:24.200 --> 31:25.300
Psychologists.
Oh...

31:25.400 --> 31:26.900
What? You're the one
who believes in them.

31:27.000 --> 31:28.300
Let's just stick to the case.

31:28.400 --> 31:32.000
We know that Father Donlan
is this harsh, judgmental guy.

31:32.100 --> 31:34.700
He keeps being sent these,
uh, problematic priests.

31:34.800 --> 31:37.000
There's McCourt,
there's Father Matt...
No proof.

31:37.200 --> 31:39.400
Yeah, but Bones, it happens.
All right? So, anyways...

31:39.500 --> 31:41.200
Father Donlan,
he's getting old,

31:41.300 --> 31:43.900
he can't deal, so he
takes action.
Old Testament action?

31:44.000 --> 31:45.900
All right, there you go again.
You're attacking God.

31:46.000 --> 31:49.100
I'm not attacking God.
He doesn't exist.
He's not scandals, okay?

31:49.200 --> 31:50.200
Quarreling?

31:50.400 --> 31:51.400
Yes, of course you are.

31:51.500 --> 31:52.600
Uh, cup of coffee,

31:52.700 --> 31:53.700
please, Vera darling.

31:54.700 --> 31:56.000
I am here to put right

31:56.100 --> 31:57.500
what has been rent asunder.

31:57.600 --> 31:58.900
Great. You've figured
out our problem.

31:59.100 --> 32:00.500
Yes.
From three meetings?

32:00.800 --> 32:03.000
I knew what your problem
was right off the bat,

32:03.100 --> 32:04.200
if you'll forgive
a cricket metaphor.

32:04.300 --> 32:06.200
The meetings were for fun.

32:08.000 --> 32:09.900
Booth never knows where to stand

32:10.100 --> 32:11.300
when he's in the lab.
Feels like

32:11.400 --> 32:13.400
teats on a bull
whenever he's there.

32:13.500 --> 32:15.600
Ditto Dr. Brennan
in the interrogation room.

32:15.700 --> 32:18.000
Simple geography,
sense of belonging,

32:18.100 --> 32:20.100
et cetera.
But that's not the main problem.

32:20.300 --> 32:21.400
He can't possibly know.

32:21.600 --> 32:22.500
Yes, I do.

32:24.100 --> 32:25.600
You're both afraid

32:25.700 --> 32:27.800
that the reason Dr. Brennan

32:27.900 --> 32:30.500
with her boyfriend Sully

32:31.600 --> 32:34.700
might have been because of her
ties to Agent Booth.

32:38.900 --> 32:39.900
You are both...

32:41.100 --> 32:42.000
quite wrong.

32:47.300 --> 32:48.600
Why didn't I go with Sully?

32:48.700 --> 32:49.900
How's he supposed to know?

32:50.000 --> 32:51.100
Sully is perfect.

32:51.300 --> 32:54.400
We communicated well.
The sex was incredible.

32:54.700 --> 32:55.500
He invited me

32:55.500 --> 32:56.700
to sail around
the South Seas

32:56.800 --> 32:58.600
in a beautiful yac for a year.

32:58.700 --> 33:00.400
I mean, why would
anyone turn that down?

33:00.700 --> 33:03.200
In my opinion, you are unable

33:03.500 --> 33:05.000
to lead a purposeless life

33:05.100 --> 33:06.000
at this stage in your

33:06.100 --> 33:08.100
psycho-social development.
Which, by the way,

33:08.200 --> 33:09.600
is a issue you should address,

33:10.000 --> 33:12.000
because a certain amount
of purposelessness

33:12.100 --> 33:14.800
is necessary to lead
a full life.
I hate psychology.

33:14.900 --> 33:16.600
You don't like it because he's
saying that all these tension

33:16.700 --> 33:18.900
between me and you
is <i>your</i> fault.

33:19.000 --> 33:20.300
On the contrary.

33:21.100 --> 33:23.500
If anything, your issues
are more pronounced

33:23.700 --> 33:25.100
given that your
behavior has been

33:25.200 --> 33:27.400
affected by what turns out
to be a quite irrational

33:27.400 --> 33:29.900
fear of being responsible
for somebody else's destiny.

33:29.900 --> 33:30.700
That makes sense.

33:30.800 --> 33:32.500
Oh, <i>now</i> you like psychology?

33:32.600 --> 33:33.700
I think you'll both

33:33.800 --> 33:36.100
be able to work together
just fine

33:36.400 --> 33:38.500
now that your minds
have been set at ease.

33:38.700 --> 33:39.900
Thank you, Vera.

33:41.300 --> 33:41.600
Ta-ta.

33:47.100 --> 33:49.500
You, uh... feel anything?

33:49.700 --> 33:50.700
Feel?

33:51.000 --> 33:52.800
Yeah. You must...

33:53.400 --> 33:54.600
feel something.

33:56.300 --> 33:57.200
I do.

33:58.400 --> 33:59.700
You know what I feel?

34:01.000 --> 34:03.600
Father Matt has been
sick a long time.

34:03.700 --> 34:05.200
He got treated for the fungus.

34:05.300 --> 34:07.100
But he hasn't shown
any signs of recovery.

34:07.200 --> 34:09.500
So?
I <i>feel</i> that's weird.

34:09.600 --> 34:11.699
I mean, his symptoms
should've cleared up by now.

34:12.100 --> 34:15.400
I feel that since Father
McCourt was poisoned...

34:15.500 --> 34:17.300
We should have
Father Matt checked

34:17.400 --> 34:18.800
for the same poison.

34:20.500 --> 34:22.000
What?
We're back.

34:22.100 --> 34:23.100
We're back.

34:23.900 --> 34:24.800
Poisoned?

34:25.000 --> 34:25.900
Yes, Father.

34:26.000 --> 34:27.100
By something
called taxin.

34:28.000 --> 34:29.300
Father McCourt
was poisoned?

34:29.699 --> 34:32.400
Poison's easily derived from
boiling yew tree needles.

34:32.500 --> 34:34.400
We have yew trees
at St. Agatha's.

34:34.500 --> 34:37.100
Symptoms include
nausea, vomiting,

34:37.400 --> 34:39.800
increased salivation,
stomach ache, diarrhea,

34:40.100 --> 34:41.699
spasms and death.

34:42.199 --> 34:45.199
Well, I have all those,
except for death.

34:45.199 --> 34:46.600
So far.

34:47.000 --> 34:49.000
We suspect the poison
weakened him,

34:49.199 --> 34:50.699
made him unable
to defend himself.

34:50.900 --> 34:53.100
Defend himself from whom?

34:53.100 --> 34:54.699
Someone much weaker
than himself.

34:54.800 --> 34:56.300
Say, an old man.

35:03.400 --> 35:03.900
Yellow.

35:04.000 --> 35:05.000
Yellow?
What does that mean?

35:05.100 --> 35:06.300
The good news is we know how

35:06.300 --> 35:07.500
to make you feel a lot better.

35:07.600 --> 35:09.300
Bad news is someone's
trying to kill you.

35:12.700 --> 35:13.600
So things are
all right?

35:14.200 --> 35:16.300
According to the psychiatrist,
we were both concerned

35:16.300 --> 35:18.300
that Booth was the reason
I didn't run off with Sully.

35:19.200 --> 35:19.800
It wasn't?

35:19.900 --> 35:21.900
No. It's because
I'm currently

35:22.000 --> 35:23.700
unable to live a life
without tangible focus.

35:23.800 --> 35:27.300
So, you know, sailing around
paradise with a man I adore...

35:27.500 --> 35:28.600
You believe that?

35:29.500 --> 35:31.100
Well, if I expect
people to defer to me

35:31.200 --> 35:32.600
as an anthropologist,
I have to concede

35:32.700 --> 35:34.200
to their fields
of expertise.

35:34.700 --> 35:35.100
Right.

35:35.200 --> 35:38.100
And our working relationship
has definitely improved, so...

35:38.900 --> 35:40.200
Maybe I should
talk to this guy.

35:41.200 --> 35:41.900
Why?

35:43.600 --> 35:46.800
Hodgins asked me to move in
with him, but I'm not sure.

35:47.300 --> 35:48.500
I mean, what's
the problem?

35:48.800 --> 35:50.000
Hodgins is perfect.

35:50.300 --> 35:52.500
I'm nuts about him.

35:55.200 --> 35:56.500
I'll call the doctor.

35:58.900 --> 36:01.100
I'm certain that I am innocent
of whatever it is

36:01.100 --> 36:02.400
you think I did this time.

36:02.700 --> 36:03.700
Can you identify

36:03.800 --> 36:05.400
this clipping, sir?

36:05.900 --> 36:07.000
 <i>Taxus baccata--</i>

36:07.100 --> 36:09.500
the European or common yew.

36:09.600 --> 36:11.600
Then you're aware
that it's poisonous.

36:11.700 --> 36:14.700
Did you bring me here
to test my botanical knowledge?

36:14.700 --> 36:17.700
Both Father McCourt and Father
Matt suffered yew poisoning.

36:18.800 --> 36:19.900
The hell you say.

36:21.100 --> 36:22.200
Is he allowed to say that?

36:22.300 --> 36:24.300
Dr. Brennan's people can prove

36:24.400 --> 36:26.000
that the poison
from the yew tree

36:26.100 --> 36:27.500
came from
your own yard.

36:28.000 --> 36:30.400
Both Fathers McCourt and Sands?

36:30.600 --> 36:32.300
It's why Father Matt
has been so sick.

36:32.400 --> 36:34.500
Can you think of
anyone else who'd want

36:34.600 --> 36:35.800
to poison these two priests,

36:36.400 --> 36:37.500
aside from you?

36:42.500 --> 36:43.100
No.

36:43.900 --> 36:45.000
No one.

36:47.300 --> 36:48.700
I'm going to need a lawyer.

36:49.300 --> 36:51.500
A damn Jesuit
would be best.

36:51.800 --> 36:53.000
Are you confessing, Father?

36:53.000 --> 36:54.300
Yes. I did it.

37:01.200 --> 37:01.700
What?

37:06.200 --> 37:07.900
When this goes to trial,
Father...

37:08.800 --> 37:10.500
you'reonna have
to place your hand

37:10.700 --> 37:11.900
on the Holy Bible

37:12.400 --> 37:15.200
and swear to God
to tell the truth.

37:15.300 --> 37:16.300
You gonna be
able to do that?

37:17.800 --> 37:18.800
What's going on?

37:19.000 --> 37:20.500
Get me my lawyer.

37:21.000 --> 37:22.200
See, I don't think
you will.

37:22.700 --> 37:23.300
Why?

37:23.800 --> 37:24.600
You didn't do it.

37:24.900 --> 37:27.200
See, it's time
to render unto Caesar.

37:36.100 --> 37:36.900
On one condition:

37:38.800 --> 37:40.000
I take the confession.

37:42.100 --> 37:44.200
I never set out
to kill Father McCourt.

37:45.100 --> 37:46.300
You poisoned him.

37:46.500 --> 37:48.400
I saw the way he looked
at James LeVay.

37:49.800 --> 37:52.000
I tried to give him
just enough poison

37:52.100 --> 37:54.000
to make him too sick
to want to...

37:55.500 --> 37:57.500
But he fell
and hit his head.

37:59.000 --> 37:59.900
He wasn't breathing.

38:00.100 --> 38:01.800
I had to make
sure he was dead.

38:02.400 --> 38:04.600
I couldn't bury him
without making sure.

38:04.700 --> 38:07.100
And the heaviest thing
she could find was the chalice.

38:07.700 --> 38:08.800
And Father Matt?

38:09.600 --> 38:10.500
Wrestling.

38:11.400 --> 38:12.700
Boys were all over him.

38:12.900 --> 38:15.300
And I knew better
this time.

38:15.900 --> 38:17.600
Less poison.

38:17.700 --> 38:20.200
Father McCourt was
a mistake, Father. I...

38:20.300 --> 38:22.900
Lorraine, there was no proof

38:23.000 --> 38:25.200
that Father McCourt
touched anyone.

38:25.600 --> 38:26.600
Only rumors.

38:26.700 --> 38:27.900
And Father Matt...

38:28.000 --> 38:29.600
You were so angry
at Father Matt.

38:29.700 --> 38:30.700
I see the way you look at him.

38:30.800 --> 38:32.600
Because he was sent here
to replace me.

38:33.400 --> 38:35.700
What you saw was my own pride,

38:35.800 --> 38:37.500
my own weakness.

38:39.200 --> 38:40.800
Father Matt is a good man.

38:41.000 --> 38:42.400
I was trying to help.

38:44.400 --> 38:45.700
I was just trying to help.

38:48.600 --> 38:49.700
Do you absolve me, Father?

38:55.300 --> 38:56.000
We're not alone

38:56.100 --> 38:57.300
with God, Lorraine.

38:58.900 --> 39:01.000
This is not that kind
of confession.

40:05.300 --> 40:06.100
Excuse us.

40:07.700 --> 40:08.500
Dr. Wyatt.

40:08.600 --> 40:10.100
We need you to
do it with her.

40:11.300 --> 40:12.600
W-Would that I could,

40:12.700 --> 40:15.800
but unfortunately,
my heart belongs to another.

40:16.200 --> 40:19.300
No, it's actually
my... boyfriend

40:20.400 --> 40:21.800
asked me to move in
with him,

40:21.900 --> 40:25.400
and I need to know
if I should or not.

40:25.600 --> 40:27.400
I told her to
talk with you.

40:29.800 --> 40:31.800
Look, I absolutely refuse
to be relegated to the role

40:31.900 --> 40:36.200
of some sort of advice columnist
or daytime television shrink.

40:36.600 --> 40:37.400
Well, Brennan says

40:37.500 --> 40:39.400
that you're the only
psychological type

40:39.500 --> 40:40.900
who's ever made
any sense to her.

40:42.100 --> 40:43.900
Yes, well, now, of course
you're flattering me,

40:44.000 --> 40:45.600
so obviously I'm helpless.

40:46.500 --> 40:47.900
All right,
so what made you think

40:48.000 --> 40:50.100
you should move in with him
in the first place?

40:50.300 --> 40:51.400
The closet test.

40:51.600 --> 40:54.200
Over half of his closet
is filled with my things.

40:54.300 --> 40:56.200
I see. And what about
your own closet?

40:56.300 --> 40:58.300
It overfloweth
with his things, does it?

40:58.400 --> 40:59.600
Uh, no.

41:00.000 --> 41:01.200
It doth not.

41:01.200 --> 41:03.100
Well, then I suggest
you wait until it does,

41:03.200 --> 41:05.100
thus rendering you
manifest equals,

41:05.200 --> 41:09.100
tabling until that day
the vexed question of

41:09.200 --> 41:10.500
who should move in with whom.

41:12.000 --> 41:12.800
He is good.

41:12.900 --> 41:13.500
I told you.

41:13.500 --> 41:15.100
As a stopgap, you should remove

41:15.200 --> 41:16.800
enough clothing from his closet

41:17.200 --> 41:19.800
so as to occupy less than
30 percent of the space.

41:20.800 --> 41:22.500
You know, the accent makes

41:22.600 --> 41:24.600
everything that you say
sound really smart.

41:25.400 --> 41:26.500
"Stopgap."

41:28.800 --> 41:30.800
No, you're not leaving,
are you, Dr. Brennan?

41:31.000 --> 41:32.300
Booth and I have to put

41:32.600 --> 41:34.400
our notes together
for the prosecutor.

41:35.700 --> 41:36.300
So...

41:36.400 --> 41:38.500
So you and Booth, um...

41:39.700 --> 41:42.000
you making any further
assumptions about each other?

41:42.200 --> 41:42.500
No.

41:43.300 --> 41:44.800
No assumptions.

41:45.700 --> 41:46.800
Thanks.

41:47.200 --> 41:47.900
Good.

41:52.400 --> 41:53.900
Well, look at that.

41:54.500 --> 41:55.800
You fixed them, too.

41:59.900 --> 42:00.700
All right, listen up,

42:00.800 --> 42:01.800
Monty Python.

42:01.900 --> 42:04.000
You got it right with
Hodgins and I, that's fine.

42:04.200 --> 42:07.200
But we both know that you are
full of it on the other thing.

42:09.400 --> 42:10.800
I have no idea
to what you refer.

42:11.300 --> 42:13.300
Brennan didn't run off
with Sully

42:13.400 --> 42:15.400
because she cannot
live a life without focus.

42:16.400 --> 42:18.100
She stayed because of Booth.

42:18.200 --> 42:21.000
Ah, now you're projecting,
Ms. Montenegro.

42:22.000 --> 42:25.500
Agent Booth and Dr. Brennan
are not you and Dr. Hodgins.

42:25.600 --> 42:27.100
I stand by
my diagnosis.

42:27.200 --> 42:28.900
You stand by the FBI.

42:29.700 --> 42:31.500
Your first priority
is to get agents

42:31.500 --> 42:32.600
back into the field,

42:32.700 --> 42:34.000
solving murders.

42:34.500 --> 42:37.400
Your romanticism is endearing,
but as the Bard says,

42:37.900 --> 42:40.500
"Lovers and madmen have such
seething brains,

42:40.600 --> 42:42.400
"such shaping fantasies,

42:42.700 --> 42:46.000
that apprehend more than cool
reason ever comprehends."

42:46.100 --> 42:50.400
He also says, "Journeys end
in lovers meeting,

42:50.600 --> 42:52.500
every wise man's
son doth know."

42:52.800 --> 42:55.300
Hm. Excellent.

42:56.300 --> 42:58.600
You betcha... Monty.

